{{italic title}}
'''''The Gardener's Labyrinth''''' or '''''The Gardeners Labyrinth''''' was an early popular [[book]] about [[gardening]].  It was written by [[Thomas Hill (author)|Thomas Hill]], using the pseudonym ''Didymus Mountain'', with [[Henry Dethick]]<ref>{{citation |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cyr9GwAACAAJ |title=The Gardeners Labyrinth|author=Henry Dethick, Didymus Mountain |date=1577}}</ref> and published in 1577.<ref>{{citation |url=http://special.lib.gla.ac.uk/exhibns/month/may2001.html |publisher=University of Glasgow |author=Julie Coleman |date=May 2001 |title=The Gardener's Labyrinth}}</ref>

